'''Krizlaws''' were native herd-beasts from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Munlali Mafir]]. Their heads resembled that of a [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] and their skin was smooth and [[Color/Legends|pink]] with small red [[Eye/Legends|eyes]]; their arms were small and tipped with three venomous claws, and their legs were large and used for pouncing. Thought to be no more intelligent than a [[Nerf/Legends|nerf]], they always hunted in packs of eleven, each individual linked together in a form of hive-mind. When one individual was wounded or killed, another would come and replace it, bringing the total back to eleven.

When the living planet of [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] passed through their [[Star system/Legends|star system]], the planet experienced a period of prolonged seismic and [[Volcano/Legends|volcanic]] activity that decimated the population of Krizlaws and even destroyed the [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Jostran]] civilization. As a result, the surviving Jostrans formed a symbiotic relationship with the Krizlaws, entering through the creatures' [[Mouth/Legends|mouths]] and finding their way to the spine and the [[Brain/Legends|brain]] where they would take over the central [[nervous system]]. The resultant Krizlaw [[Species/Legends|species]] now contained their animal [[Hive mind/Legends|hive-mind]] of eleven linked individuals but now also had eleven intelligent Jostran "rider's" joining the collective.

